Here are the list of problems that I am seeing within your pom file which you need to fix them

 - `&lt;scope&gt;Tests.SubTotalTest&lt;/scope&gt;`

As pointed out by others, this is not a valid value for scope. Please either remove it (it would then default to `compile` which means that the dependency is going to be available for all java classes in both `src/main/java` and in `src/test/java`)

 - `&lt;version&gt;RELEASE&lt;/version&gt;`

This does not resolve to any proper version. Please replace this with an actual version `7.4.0` (latest TestNG released version as of today) or use a proper maven variable (I don&#39;t think you need that right now because it would be an overkill)

For your tests to be executed as defined in your suite xml file, you need to configure surefire plugin accordingly. If not done, surefire plugin will always run all the test classes it can find (by default it looks for files that have `Test` (or) `TestCase` in the file name). You can learn more about this on the surefire plugin documentation.


&lt;!-- language: xml --&gt;

    &lt;plugin&gt;
    	&lt;groupId&gt;org.apache.maven.plugins&lt;/groupId&gt;
    	&lt;artifactId&gt;maven-surefire-plugin&lt;/artifactId&gt;
    	&lt;version&gt;3.0.0-M5&lt;/version&gt;
    	&lt;configuration&gt;
    		&lt;suiteXmlFiles&gt;
    			&lt;suiteXmlFile&gt;testng.xml&lt;/suiteXmlFile&gt;
    		&lt;/suiteXmlFiles&gt;
    	&lt;/configuration&gt;
    &lt;/plugin&gt;

For the tag `&lt;suiteXmlFile&gt;` add the location of your `testng.xml` file (relative file location from the root directory of your project) and then surefire plugin will ONLY run the tests that are mentioned in the suite file.

Read more about maven surefire plugin from their documentation at http://maven.apache.org/surefire/maven-surefire-plugin/examples/testng.html

